          "reviewBody": "Here’s a **well-written positive review** you can use or post:\n\n---\n\n**⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Excellent School with a Holistic Approach**\n\nRockwell International School offers a wonderful learning environment that focuses on the overall development of children. The school strikes a great balance between academics, extracurricular activities, and life skills, helping students grow into confident and well-rounded individuals.\n\nThe teachers are highly dedicated, caring, and approachable. They pay individual attention to students and encourage curiosity, creativity, and critical thinking. The curriculum is engaging and thoughtfully designed to make learning enjoyable rather than stressful.\n\nThe campus and facilities are impressive—spacious classrooms, well-equipped labs, sports facilities, and activity areas create a positive and stimulating atmosphere. Safety and security measures are also well maintained, giving parents peace of mind.\n\nWhat truly sets Rockwell apart is its nurturing and supportive culture. Students are encouraged to explore their talents, express themselves freely, and develop strong values along with academic excellence. Overall, Rockwell International School is an excellent choice for parents looking for quality education with a holistic vision.\n\n",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Rockwell International School - Gandipet"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Pratibha"
          },
          "datePublished": "2026-01-14",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "2",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I would like to share some genuine feedback with the intention of helping the school create an even more positive and encouraging environment for students.\nWhile the school circulates information about external competitions, beyond this there is unfortunately no encouragement or guidance provided by the school. The entire responsibility is left to the child and parents. Even when a child gets selected or performs well, there is no follow-up support, guidance for next steps, or even basic appreciation or congratulations. A little motivation and acknowledgment from the school can go a long way in boosting a child’s confidence.\nI would like to clarify that I have no complaints regarding the Principal. However, I am quite disappointed with the approach of the Middle School Coordinator, Madam Sharavanya. The general impression given is that a “good child” is one who sits quietly, while children who are talkative, expressive, or energetic are labeled as naughty or indisciplined. Sports and playtime are often cancelled if children are seen talking or enjoying themselves.\nChildren are children — they learn, grow, and express themselves through interaction and play. When a child is performing well academically, co-curricular, and overall, it is disheartening to see their natural enthusiasm and childhood joy being suppressed. School should be a place children love coming to, not a place that feels restrictive or suffocating.\nActive, intelligent, and smart children are often extroverts. Their ability to communicate, express opinions, and engage socially should be seen as strengths, not flaws. Expecting children to behave like adults by being silent and passive takes away their childhood and impacts their emotional well-being.\nWe strongly feel that a coordinator should be child-friendly, approachable, and supportive. Unfortunately, most responses to parents’ requests are negative, which was not the case with the earlier coordinator, Ms. Saama Ma’am. Children today appear genuinely scared rather than comfortable approaching the coordinator, which is concerning.\nI sincerely request the school management to please look into this matter and consider appointing coordinators and teachers who understand a child’s perspective, encourage talent, motivate students, and celebrate their achievements. Positive guidance and appreciation are essential, especially for children who are doing well and excelling in multiple areas.\nPlease do not take away a child’s childhood. Let school be a space where children feel safe, happy, motivated, and inspired to grow.\nThank you for your time and consideration. I hope this feedback will be taken in the right spirit for the betterment of the children and the school.",
