        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Rockwell International School - Gandipet"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Anonymous"
          },
          "datePublished": "2025-11-07",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "\nI am highly disappointed with the behaviour of the Middle School Coordinator, Ms. Shravanya. It has been observed that she often targets a few specific children and does not allow them to share their side of the story. Her approach usually involves raising her voice, insulting, or punishing the child, which is very disheartening.\n\nI sincerely request the school management to kindly look into this matter. No child at Rockwell should ever go through mental distress or feel discouraged. We have all heard of unfortunate incidents like that of Amaira from Neerja Modi School, and I truly hope such situations never arise here.\n\nA coordinator or teacher should be patient, understanding, and empathetic. Children naturally have high energy levels — this should be guided and channelled positively, not handled through scolding or humiliation. Having energy and enthusiasm is a sign of a healthy, active mind, not a fault.\n\nMy child is very intelligent but is repeatedly being singled out by Ms. Shravanya, which has become extremely concerning for us as parents. I kindly urge the school to ensure that teachers and coordinators are trained to handle students with patience and to motivate them positively, as is done in many schools abroad. Constant punishment and criticism can deeply affect a young and tender mind.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
